com.communote.plugins.api.rest.resource

Class AbstractResourceHandler<C,E,D,G,L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.communote.plugins.api.rest.resource.AbstractResourceHandler<C,E,D,G,L>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - create resource parameter
    E - edit resource parameter
    D - delete resource parameter
    G - get resource parameter
    L - list resource parameter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultResourceHandler

    public abstract class AbstractResourceHandler<C,E,D,G,L>
extends Object
    A handler of a a REST API resource. The handler performs invocation to the supplied validator on each handling method. In the case no exceptions occurred the internal handling method (which should be implemented by subclasses) is invoked. A validator MUST be set (through setValidator method) during the concrete resource handler construction
    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/
